thread.title: Shawnee tops Holy Cross in Coaches Tournament
thread.title_full: Shawnee tops Holy Cross in Coaches Tournament

title: Shawnee tops Holy Cross in Coaches Tournament
text:
Kayla Harris had two goals for host St. Joseph in a 6-2 win over Doane Academy. Taylor Breitzman, Nikki Cirigliano, Katie Lillia, and Jana Martini also scored. Field Hockey Sam Derkas scored twice, helping host Seneca defeat Lenape, 3-0, in Olympic Conference action. Abigail Regn had a goal and Kasey Mitchell had an assist.
Burlington County League. Madison Aguanno scored two goals for host Delran in a 4-0 defeat of Maple Shade. Alexis Rider and Becky Howard had assists. Boys' Soccer Kyle Leach scored a goal in each half, helping Pitman defeat host Gloucester Catholic, 3-2, in Tri-County Classic play. Pitman is guaranteed at least a share of the Tri-County Classic title. Grant DeClement also had a goal. 
Burlington County League. Cody LaCava scored two goals for New Egypt in its 4-1 win on the road against Pennsauken. Dan Ryniec and Andrew Agostinacchio also scored. Tim Blomgren made 15 saves.
